No fewer than twelve people have reportedly died in a ghastly motor accident in Ebonyi State. It was gathered that the tragic incident happened at Ezillo in Ishielu Local Government Area of the state, along the even busy Enugu-Abakaliki Highway. The Federal Road Safety Commission (FRSC) Sector Commander,Â Uche Chukwurah, who confirmed the incident said the road crash happened at about 10 am on Tuesday, saying the accident involved an unmarked truck and a white shuttle bus with registration number EBJ 350 XA. The FRSC boss said ten females and two males on board were among the deceased. Chukwurah said two injured passengers were receiving treatment at Alex-Ekwueme Federal University Teaching Hospital, Abakiliki.